text: The Northern Metropolitan Region is an electoral region of the Victorian Legislative Council, the upper house of the Victorian Parliament. It is located in the northern part of Melbourne. The region includes the Legislative Assembly (lower house) electoral districts of Broadmeadows, Brunswick, Essendon, Greenvale, Kalkallo, Melbourne, Northcote, Pascoe Vale, Preston, Richmond and Thomastown. ==Election results== ==References== Category:Electoral regions of Victoria Category:2006 establishments in Australia
